channel.title: REP++ (Port 43594 problems) wtf?
channel.description:
Hello I am having problems getting port 43594 open
I have it open in my modem. [url=https://www.dropbox.com/s/cm7s7hotkqik2fe/1.bmp]https://www.dropbox.com/s/cm7s7hotkqik2fe/1.bmp[/url]
I have my firewall set up like this [url=https://www.dropbox.com/s/uo0dh9tzqmv59l8/5.bmp]https://www.dropbox.com/s/uo0dh9tzqmv59l8/5.bmp[/url]
I even downloaded the static ip application because portforward.com said i needed it to allow people to get acces to my port.
But everytime I use portchecker I get this [url=https://www.dropbox.com/s/7ev4u5x33298e21/4.bmp]https://www.dropbox.com/s/7ev4u5x33298e21/4.bmp[/url]
And no one can connect to my server. I have the no-ip set up and my no-ip in my client side client.java
If anyone has any ideas please let me know
